- "Most recent" refers to the latest date or timestamp in the respective records;
- "Expiry details" include the expiry date and batch number;
- "Compliance details" include the compliance date, type, and status;
- "Notification details" include the notification date, message, and type;
- "Access logs" include the access time, action, and location.

- "wilting" refers to products that are near expiration or have already expired;
- "petals" refers to the total number of batches of the product;
- "flowers" refers to the medicinal products;
- "types" refers to the categories of medicinal products.

- 'flowers (products)' refers to medicinal products;
- 'caretakers (MAHs)' refers to Marketing Authorization Holders;
- 'lifespan (shelf life)' refers to the shelf life of product variants;
- 'bloom (last)' refers to the duration the product remains effective or usable.

